  ["a4dc302c-ab71-4d7b-a10a-3116a778e8d5", true, "Ambition Institute self-directed study materials", "## Welcome\n\n> “Every teacher needs to improve, not because they are not good enough, but because they can be even better.” – Dylan Wiliam\n\nWelcome to the Early Career Teachers programme. This programme harnesses the Early Career Framework (ECF) to help NQTs develop their teaching during the first few years of their career.\n\nWe have drawn on the best available evidence around how professionals learn to create a programme that will not only have a lasting impact on NQT knowledge and practice, but will do so whilst respecting the busy and demanding working lives of teachers.\n\nWe believe that effective teaching is one of the biggest levers we have for improving the experiences, outcomes and life chances of the pupils in our care. It is a privilege to support you on your journey to keep getting better.\n\n{button}[Read the introduction](http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/introduction/){/button}\n\n{button secondary}[Download all teacher materials](https://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/09/EarlyCareerTeachers_TextbookDigital_Teachers_v3-compressed.pdf){/button}\n\nFor guidance on using these materials, see the [ECF Teacher Handbook (PDF)](http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/08/Ambition-EarlyCareerTeachers_2020_TeacherHandbook_Guidebook_FULL_DEV.pdf).\n\n## The strands\n\n$Accordion\n$Heading\nBehaviour\n$EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/1-strand-fundamentals-and-contracting/\">\n  B1. Strand fundamentals and contracting\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/2-routines/\">\n  B2. Routines\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/3-instructions/\">\n  B3. Instructions\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/4-directing-attention/\">\n  B4. Directing attention\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/5-low-level-disruption/\">\n  B5. Low-level disruption\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/6-consistency/\">\n  B6. Consistency\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/7-positive-learning-environment/\">\n  B7. Positive learning environment\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/8-structured-support-of-learning/\">\n  B8. Structured support of learning\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/9-challenge/\">\n  B9. Challenge\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/10-independent-practice/\">\n  B10. Independent practice\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/11-pairs-and-groups/\">\n  B11. Pairs and groups\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/1-behaviour/12-upholding-high-expectations/\">\n  B12. Upholding high expectations\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Instruction $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/1-strand-fundamentals-and-re-contracting/\">\n  I1. Strand fundamentals and re-contracting\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/2-identifying-learning-content/\">\n  I2. Identifying learning content\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/3-instruction-for-memory/\">\n  I3. Instruction for memory\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/4-prior-knowledge/\">\n  I4. Prior knowledge\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/5-teacher-exposition/\">\n  I5. Teacher exposition\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/6-adapting-teaching/\">\n  I6. Adapting teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/7-practice-challenge-and-success/\">\n  I7. Practice, challenge and success\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/8-explicit-learning/\">\n  I8. Explicit learning\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/9-scaffolding/\">\n  I9. Scaffolding\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/10-questioning/\">\n  I10. Questioning\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/2-instruction/11-classroom-talk/\">\n  I11. Classroom talk\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/12-instruction/feedback/\">\n  I12. Feedback\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Subject $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/1-strand-fundamentals-and-re-contracting/\">\n  S1. Strand fundamentals and re-contracting\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/2-planning-backwards-from-learning-goals/\">\n  S2. Planning backwards from learning goals\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/3-types-of-knowledge/\">\n  S3. Types of knowledge\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/4-gaps-and-misconceptions/\">\n  S4. Gaps and misconceptions\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/5-acquisition-before-application/\">\n  S5. Acquisition before application\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/6-promoting-deep-learning/\">\n  S6. Promoting deep learning\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/7-developing-pupils-literacy/\">\n  S7. Developing pupils’ literacy\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/8-sharing-academic-expectations/\">\n  S8. Sharing academic expectations\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/9-assessing-for-formative-purposes/\">\n  S9. Assessing for formative purposes\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/10-examining-pupils-responses/\">\n  S10. Examining pupils’ responses\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3-subject/11-adapting-lessons-to-meet-pupils-needs/\">\n  S11. Adapting lessons to meet pupils needs\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ambition/ambition-institute/self-directed-study-materials/3.subject/feedback/\">\n  S12. Feedback\n</a>\n$EndContent $EndAccordion\n\n", 4, "483d68d3-aae6-416c-b9ec-6103fe2cd067"],
  ["d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", true, "EDT self-directed study materials", "## Welcome\n\nAcross the two years, ECTs will work through 12 Blocks in total, one per half term. Each Block has been designed based on international best practice of effective professional development, and includes interactive self-study materials that explain the research behind the Early Career Framework and give exemplifications of what this looks like in the classroom. There is also protected time in Year 1 as part of these materials to observe colleagues and to be observed.\n\nEach Block provides ECTs with the time to:\n\n- **Learn** the content from the Early Career Framework\n- Put the learning into **practice** with suggestions for classroom practice\n- **Reflect** on their professional and personal development.\n\nFor more information on the programme structure and suggestions on well-being and workload, see the [Overview of the Core Induction Programme (PDF)](http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/08/Overview-of-EDTs-Core-Induction-Programme.pdf)\n\n## Year 1\n\n$Accordion\n$Heading\nOverview\n$EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\nYear 1 is an introduction to the key themes and statements in the Early Career Framework. The focus is on helping Early Career Teachers (ECTs) to establish themselves in the classroom, drawing on the best international evidence for what works in education. ECTs will work on core principles and techniques of effective teaching, including lesson planning, expositions, assessment, feedback and managing behaviour. Throughout each Block (module) they will find practical, accessible self-study activities to support their development. These will be further supplemented by regular sessions with their Mentor and training sessions led by an expert practitioner. These sessions are designed to support ECTs to translate the research into their classroom, with opportunities to discuss research, observe colleagues, practise new techniques and reflect on their progress and next steps.\n$EndContent\n$Heading\nBlock 1: Establishing a positive climate for learning\n$EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/establishing-a-positive-climate-for-learning/1-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block/\">\n  Activity 1.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/establishing-a-positive-climate-for-learning/1-2-understanding-the-evidence-the-importance-of-expectations-routines-and-relationships/\">\n  Activity 1.2: Understanding the evidence: The importance of expectations,\n  routines and relationships\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/establishing-a-positive-climate-for-learning/1-3-learning-about-classroom-routines/\">\n  Activity 1.3: Learning about… classroom routines\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/establishing-a-positive-climate-for-learning/1-4-learning-about-maintaining-consistently-high-behavioural-expectations/\">\n  Activity 1.4: Learning about… Maintaining consistently high behavioural\n  expectations\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/establishing-a-positive-climate-for-learning/1-5-developing-your-teaching-your-role-in-establishing-positive-behaviour/\">\n  Activity 1.5: Developing your teaching – your role in establishing positive\n  behaviour\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/establishing-a-positive-climate-for-learning/1-6-observations/\">\n  Activity 1.6: Observations\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/establishing-a-positive-climate-for-learning/1-7-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 1.7: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 2: How pupils learn ‒ memory and cognition $EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/how-pupils-learn-%e2%80%92-memory-and-cognition/2-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block/\">\n  Activity 2.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/how-pupils-learn-%e2%80%92-memory-and-cognition/2-2-understanding-the-evidence/\">\n  Activity 2.2: Understanding the evidence\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/how-pupils-learn-%e2%80%92-memory-and-cognition/2-3-learning-about-prior-knowledge-misconceptions-and-worked-examples/\">\n  Activity 2.3: Learning about… prior knowledge, misconceptions and worked\n  examples\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/how-pupils-learn-%e2%80%92-memory-and-cognition/2-4-developing-your-teaching/\">\n  Activity 2.4: Developing your teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/how-pupils-learn-%e2%80%92-memory-and-cognition/2-5-improving-your-teaching-lesson-observations/\">\n  Activity 2.5: Improving your teaching – lesson observations\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/how-pupils-learn-%e2%80%92-memory-and-cognition/2-6-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 2.6: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 3: Developing effective classroom practice ‒ teaching\nand adapting $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/3-developing-effective-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-teaching-and-adapting/3-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block/\">\n  {\" \"}\n  3.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/3-developing-effective-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-teaching-and-adapting/3-2-understanding-the-evidence-1-effective-teaching/\">\n  3.2: Understanding the evidence 1: effective teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/3-developing-effective-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-teaching-and-adapting/3-3-understanding-the-evidence-2-metacognition-and-teaching/\">\n  3.3: Understanding the evidence 2: metacognition and teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/3-developing-effective-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-teaching-and-adapting/3-4-learning-about-adaptive-teaching/\">\n  3.4: Learning about adaptive teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/3-developing-effective-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-teaching-and-adapting/3-5-developing-your-teaching/\">\n  3.5: Developing your teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/3-developing-effective-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-teaching-and-adapting/3-6-improving-your-teaching-lesson-observations/\">\n  3.6: Improving your teaching: lesson observations\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/3-developing-effective-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-teaching-and-adapting/3-7-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  3.7: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 4: The importance of subject and curriculum knowledge\n$EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/4-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/4-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block-2/\">\n  Activity 4.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/4-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/4-2-understanding-the-evidence/\">\n  Activity 4.2: Understanding the evidence\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/4-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/4-3-learning-about-literacy/\">\n  Activity 4.3: Learning about literacy\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/4-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/4-4-developing-your-teaching/\">\n  Activity 4.4: Developing your teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/4-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/4-5-improving-your-teaching-lesson-observations/\">\n  Activity 4.5: Improving your teaching – lesson observations\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/4-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/4-6-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 4.6: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 5: Assessment, feedback and questioning $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/5-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/5-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block-2-2/\">\n  Activity 5.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/5-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/5-2-understanding-the-evidence/\">\n  Activity 5.2: Understanding the evidence\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/5-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/5-3-learning-about-questioning-and-high-quality-classroom-talk/\">\n  Activity 5.3: Learning about questioning and high-quality classroom talk\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/5-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/5-4-developing-your-teaching-assessment-and-questioning/\">\n  Activity 5.4: Developing your teaching – Assessment and questioning\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/5-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/5-5-improving-your-teaching-lesson-observations/\">\n  Activity 5.5: Improving your teaching: lesson observations\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/5-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/5-6-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 5.6: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 6: A people profession $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/6-a-people-profession/6-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block-2/\">\n  Activity 6.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/6-a-people-profession/6-2-understanding-the-evidence-a-people-profession/\">\n  Activity 6.2: Understanding the evidence: A people profession{\" \"}\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/6-a-people-profession/6-3-effective-professional-relationships/\">\n  Activity 6.3: Effective professional relationships\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/6-a-people-profession/6-4-working-with-the-senco/\">\n  Activity 6.4: Working with the SENCO\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/6-a-people-profession/6-5-working-effectively-with-teaching-assistants/\">\n  Activity 6.5: Working effectively with teaching assistants\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/6-a-people-profession/6-6-observations/\">\n  Activity 6.6: Observations\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/6-a-people-profession/6-7-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 6.7: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $EndAccordion\n\n## Year 2\n\nNote: There are no self-directed study materials for Block 12\n\n$Accordion\n$Heading\nOverview\n$EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\nThe structure of the Blocks in Year 2 replicates that of Year 1. Any remaining statements from the Early Career Framework will be covered, and many of the same themes from Year 1 will be revisited in greater depth to strengthen and further ECTs’ practice. During Year 2, the focus is on mastering key ideas in the Early Career Framework. ECTs will be encouraged to reflect on the links between themes, in the light of their increasing knowledge and developing practice. They will continue to work with their Mentor to reflect on the progress they have made, and by the end of the year they will identify future opportunities for development or specialisation for the next stage of their career. Training sessions provide additional support and access to a supportive peer network of other Early Career Teachers.\n$EndContent\n$Heading\nBlock 7: Embedding a positive climate for learning\n$EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/7-embedding-a-positive-climate-for-learning/7-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block/\">\n  Activity 7.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block{\" \"}\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/7-embedding-a-positive-climate-for-learning/7-3-developing-your-teaching-supporting-pupils-to-achieve-with-challenging-content/\">\n  Activity 7.2: Understanding the evidence: Pupil motivation\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/7-embedding-a-positive-climate-for-learning/7-2-understanding-the-evidence-pupil-motivation/\">\n  Activity 7.3: Developing your teaching – supporting pupils to achieve with\n  challenging content\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/7-embedding-a-positive-climate-for-learning/7-4-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 7.4: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 8: How pupils learn – making it stick $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/8-how-pupils-learn-making-it-stick/8-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block/\">\n  Activity 8.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/8-how-pupils-learn-making-it-stick/8-2-understanding-the-evidence/\">\n  Activity 8.2: Understanding the evidence\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/8-how-pupils-learn-making-it-stick/8-3-developing-your-teaching/\">\n  Activity 8.3: Developing your teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/8-how-pupils-learn-making-it-stick/8-4-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 8.4: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 9: Enhancing classroom practice ‒ grouping and tailoring\n$EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/9-enhancing-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-grouping-and-tailoring/9-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block/\">\n  Activity 9.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/9-enhancing-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-grouping-and-tailoring/9-2-understanding-the-evidence/\">\n  Activity 9.2: Understanding the evidence\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/9-enhancing-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-grouping-and-tailoring/9-3-developing-your-teaching/\">\n  Activity 9.3: Developing your teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/9-enhancing-classroom-practice-%e2%80%92-grouping-and-tailoring/9-4-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 9.4: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 10: Revisiting the importance of subject and curriculum\nknowledge $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/10-revisiting-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/10-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block/\">\n  Activity 10.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/10-revisiting-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/10-2-curriculum-design-around-the-big-ideas/\">\n  Activity 10.2: Curriculum design around the big ideas\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/10-revisiting-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/10-3-developing-your-teaching/\">\n  Activity 10.3: Developing your teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/10-revisiting-the-importance-of-subject-and-curriculum-knowledge/10-4-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 10.4: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Block 11: Deepening assessment, feedback and questioning $EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/11-deepening-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/11-1-what-you-will-learn-and-video-introduction-to-the-block/\">\n  Activity 11.1: What you will learn, and video introduction to the Block\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/11-deepening-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/11-2-understanding-the-evidence/\">\n  Activity 11.2: Understanding the evidence\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/11-deepening-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/11-3-learning-about-developing-efficient-and-effective-approaches-to-assessment/\">\n  Activity 11.3: Learning about developing efficient and effective approaches to\n  assessment\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/11-deepening-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/11-4-developing-your-teaching/\">\n  Activity 11.4: Developing your teaching\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/edt/edt-early-career-framework/self-directed-study-materials/11-deepening-assessment-feedback-and-questioning/11-5-reflecting-on-learning/\">\n  Activity 11.5: Reflecting on learning\n</a>\n$EndContent $EndAccordion\n\n", 4, "d3bee90a-397e-4826-915a-f2874e4cbde7"],
  ["441979d3-787c-42bd-9072-2309125ef709", true, "Teach First self-directed study material", "The online study materials consist of six modules. You will complete one module per half-term in your first year of the programme. Each module has been broken down into weekly sessions to provide you with research informed, bitesize information on best practice.\n\nThroughout the online study materials, you will be prompted to complete activities and reflect on your practice, considering what you are doing well and how you could improve. It is important you invest time in these activities as being a reflective practitioner is vital for improvement at any stage of your career.\n\n$Accordion\n$Heading\nModule 1: How can you create an effective learning environment?\n$EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/1-how-can-you-create-an-effective-learning-environment/1-establishing-effective-routines-51-minutes/\">\n  Session 1. Establishing effective routines (51 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/1-how-can-you-create-an-effective-learning-environment/2-creating-a-positive-and-respectful-classroom-environment-30-minutes/\">\n  Session 2. Creating a positive and respectful classroom environment (30\n  minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/1-how-can-you-create-an-effective-learning-environment/3-addressing-low-level-behaviour-40-minutes/\">\n  Session 3. Addressing low-level behaviour (40 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/1-how-can-you-create-an-effective-learning-environment/4-addressing-persistent-and-challenging-behaviour-50-minutes/\">\n  Session 4. Addressing persistent and challenging behaviour (50 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/1-how-can-you-create-an-effective-learning-environment/5-developing-pupils-intrinsic-motivation-40-minutes/\">\n  Session 5. Developing pupils’ intrinsic motivation (40 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/1-how-can-you-create-an-effective-learning-environment/6-holding-high-expectations-and-maintaining-engagement-50-minutes/\">\n  Session 6. Holding high expectations and maintaining engagement (50 minutes)\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 2: How do pupils learn? $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/2-how-do-pupils-learn/1-the-working-and-long-term-memory-55-minutes/\">\n  Session 1. The working and long-term memory (55 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/2-how-do-pupils-learn/2-considering-how-to-introduce-new-knowledge-to-pupils-60-minutes/\">\n  Session 2. Considering how to introduce new knowledge to pupils (60 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/2-how-do-pupils-learn/3-using-worked-and-partially-completed-examples-45-minutes/\">\n  Session 3. Using worked and partially completed examples (45 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/2-how-do-pupils-learn/4-helping-pupils-remember-80-minutes/\">\n  Session 4. Helping pupils remember (80 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/2-how-do-pupils-learn/5-introduction-to-metacognition-15-minutes/\">\n  Session 5. Introduction to Metacognition (15 minutes)\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 3: What makes classroom practice effective? $EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/3-what-makes-classroom-practice-effective/1-review-of-previous-learning-15-minutes/\">\n  Session 1. Review of previous learning (15 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/3-what-makes-classroom-practice-effective/2-explanations-and-modelling-65-mins/\">\n  Session 2. Explanations and Modelling (65 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/3-what-makes-classroom-practice-effective/3-guided-practice-60-mins/\">\n  Session 3. Guided Practice (60 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/3-what-makes-classroom-practice-effective/4-independent-practice-60-mins/\">\n  Session 4. Independent Practice (60 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/3-what-makes-classroom-practice-effective/5-questioning-60-mins/\">\n  Session 5. Questioning (60 minutes)\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 4: How can you use assessment and feedback to greatest\neffect? $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/4-how-can-you-use-assessment-and-feedback-to-greatest-effect/1-what-makes-assessment-effective-50-mins/\">\n  Session 1. What Makes Assessment Effective? (50 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/4-how-can-you-use-assessment-and-feedback-to-greatest-effect/2-planning-for-effective-assessment-50-mins/\">\n  Session 2. Planning for Effective Assessment (50 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/4-how-can-you-use-assessment-and-feedback-to-greatest-effect/3-monitoring-misconceptions-45-mins/\">\n  Session 3. Monitoring Misconceptions (45 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/4-how-can-you-use-assessment-and-feedback-to-greatest-effect/4-making-feedback-purposeful-and-manageable-part-1-55-mins/\">\n  Session 4. Making Feedback Purposeful and Manageable, Part 1: What does\n  effective feedback look like? (55 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/4-how-can-you-use-assessment-and-feedback-to-greatest-effect/5-making-feedback-purposeful-and-manageable-part-2-35-mins/\">\n  Session 5. Making Feedback Purposeful and Manageable, Part 2: Effective peer\n  and self-assessment (35 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/4-how-can-you-use-assessment-and-feedback-to-greatest-effect/6-summative-assessment-30-mins/\">\n  Session 6. Summative Assessment (30 minutes)\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 5: How can you support all pupils to succeed? $EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/5-how-can-you-support-all-pupils-to-succeed/1-supporting-all-pupils-to-access-the-curriculum-developing-high-quality-oral-language-42-minutes/\">\n  Session 1. Supporting all pupils to access the curriculum – developing\n  high-quality oral language (42 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/5-how-can-you-support-all-pupils-to-succeed/2-supporting-all-pupils-to-access-the-curriculum-developing-reading-and-writing-45-minutes/\">\n  Session 2. Supporting all pupils to access the curriculum – developing reading\n  and writing (45 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/5-how-can-you-support-all-pupils-to-succeed/3-further-developing-prior-knowledge-35-minutes/\">\n  Session 3. Further developing prior knowledge (35 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/5-how-can-you-support-all-pupils-to-succeed/4-providing-additional-scaffolds-60-minutes/\">\n  Session 4. Providing additional scaffolds (60 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/5-how-can-you-support-all-pupils-to-succeed/5-the-send-code-of-practice-30-minutes/\">\n  Session 5. The SEND code of practice (30 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/5-how-can-you-support-all-pupils-to-succeed/6-teaching-pupils-who-require-a-greater-level-of-support-50-minutes/\">\n  Session 6. Teaching pupils who require a greater level of support (50 minutes)\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 6: How to design a coherent curriculum $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/6-how-to-design-a-coherent-curriculum/1-what-is-the-purpose-of-a-curriculum-25-mins/\">\n  Session 1. What is the purpose of a curriculum? (25 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/6-how-to-design-a-coherent-curriculum/2-identifying-concepts-knowledge-and-skills-50-mins/\">\n  Session 2. Identifying concepts, knowledge and skills (50 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/6-how-to-design-a-coherent-curriculum/3-sequencing-teaching-and-learning-55-mins/\">\n  Session 3. Sequencing teaching and learning (55 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/6-how-to-design-a-coherent-curriculum/4-helping-pupils-master-important-concepts-knowledge-and-skills-part-1-45-mins/\">\n  Session 4. Helping pupils master important concepts, knowledge and skills –\n  Part 1 (45 minutes)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/6-how-to-design-a-coherent-curriculum/5-helping-pupils-master-important-concepts-knowledge-and-skills-part-2-35-mins/\">\n  Session 5. Helping pupils master important concepts, knowledge and skills –\n  Part 2 (35 mins)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/teachfirst/teach-first/self-directed-study-material/6-how-to-design-a-coherent-curriculum/6-supporting-pupils-to-build-increasingly-complex-mental-models-60-mins/\">\n  Session 6. Supporting pupils to build increasingly complex mental models (60\n  minutes)\n</a>\n$EndContent $EndAccordion\n\n", 4, "2a9a661e-777f-4a5a-8b17-fc91f2e66796"],
  ["b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", true, "UCL self-directed study materials", "Any topics not listed below are for mentors or part of the Full Induction Programme only.\n\n$Accordion\n$Heading\nModule 1: Enabling pupil learning\n$EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/understanding-teachers-as-role-models/\">\n  Week 2: Understanding teachers as role models\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-establishing-the-learning-environment/\">\n  Week 3: Establishing the learning environment\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/5-understanding-pupils-as-learners/\">\n  Week 5: Understanding pupils as learners\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/6-managing-behaviour/\">\n  Week 6: Managing behaviour\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 2: Engaging pupils in learning $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/2-engaging-pupils-in-learning/2-prior-knowledge-memory-and-misconceptions/\">\n  Week 2: Prior knowledge, memory and misconceptions\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/2-engaging-pupils-in-learning/3-literacy-and-learning/\">\n  Week 3: Literacy and learning\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/2-engaging-pupils-in-learning/4-consolidation-of-learning/\">\n  Week 4: Consolidation of learning\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/2-engaging-pupils-in-learning/5-curriculum-and-subject-knowledge/\">\n  Week 5: Curriculum and subject knowledge\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 3: Developing quality pedagogy $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-developing-quality-pedagogy/2-implementing-effective-modelling/\">\n  Week 2: Implementing effective modelling\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-developing-quality-pedagogy/3-introducing-new-material-in-steps-using-exposition-and-questioning/\">\n  Week 3: Introducing new material in steps using exposition and questioning\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-developing-quality-pedagogy/4-modelling-metacognitive-strategies/\">\n  Week 4: Modelling metacognitive strategies\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-developing-quality-pedagogy/5-developing-high-quality-classroom-talk/\">\n  Week 5: Developing high-quality classroom talk\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-developing-quality-pedagogy/8-using-groupings-to-support-specific-needs/\">\n  Week 8: Using groupings to support specific needs\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-developing-quality-pedagogy/9-building-on-pupils-prior-knowledge-through-formative-assessment/\">\n  Week 9: Building on pupils’ prior knowledge through formative assessment\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-developing-quality-pedagogy/10-making-new-concepts-accessible-through-targeted-support/\">\n  Week 10: Making new concepts accessible through targeted support\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/3-developing-quality-pedagogy/11-meeting-individual-needs-and-balancing-workload/\">\n  Week 11: Meeting individual needs and balancing workload\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 4: Making productive use of assessment $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/4-making-productive-use-of-assessment/1-fundamental-principles-of-effective-assessment-1/\">\n  Week 1: Fundamental principles of effective assessment (1)\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/4-making-productive-use-of-assessment/3-applying-good-assessment-practice-in-the-classroom/\">\n  Week 3: Applying good assessment practice in the classroom\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/4-making-productive-use-of-assessment/4-giving-high-quality-feedback/\">\n  Week 4: Giving high-quality feedback\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/4-making-productive-use-of-assessment/5-planning-effective-and-manageable-marking-and-feedback/\">\n  Week 5: Planning effective and manageable marking and feedback\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 5: Fulfilling professional responsibilities $EndHeading\n$Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/5-fulfilling-professional-responsibilities/6-revisiting-professional-development/\">\n  Week 6: Revisiting professional development\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 6: Enabling pupil learning $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/6-enabling-pupil-learning/3-what-is-evidence-telling-us-about-the-effects-upon-their-pupils-of-how-the-ect-sets-high-expectations-and-manages-behaviour-effectively/\">\n  Week 3: What is evidence telling us about the effects upon their pupils of how\n  the ECT sets high expectations and manages behaviour effectively?\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 7: Engaging pupils in learning $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/7-engaging-pupils-in-learning/3-in-their-focus-area-what-impact-is-the-ect-having-on-their-pupils/\">\n  Week 3: In their focus area, what impact is the ECT having on their pupils?\n</a>\n$EndContent $Heading Module 8: Developing quality pedagogy and making productive\nuse of assessment $EndHeading $Summary\n\n$EndSummary\n$Content\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/8-developing-quality-pedagogy-and-making-productive-use-of-assessment/8-developing-quality-pedagogy-and-making-productive-use-of-assessment-2/\">\n  Week 2: What is evidence telling us about the effects upon their pupils of the\n  ECT’s practice in relation to Standards 4, 5 and 6?\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/8-developing-quality-pedagogy-and-making-productive-use-of-assessment/8-what-is-evidence-telling-us-about-the-effects-upon-their-pupils-of-the-ects-practice-in-relation-to-standards-4-5-and-6/\">\n  Week 8: What is evidence telling us about the effects upon their pupils of the\n  ECT’s practice in relation to Standards 4, 5 and 6?\n</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.early-career-framework.education.gov.uk/ucl/ucl/2-understanding-teachers-as-role-models/8-developing-quality-pedagogy-and-making-productive-use-of-assessment/13-the-impacts-upon-the-ect-of-their-inquiry/\">\n  Week 13: The impacts upon the ECT of their inquiry\n</a>\n$EndContent $EndAccordion\n\n", 4, "bd440c0b-b285-4092-89d6-891bb5a5f4ae"]
])
CourseModule.import([:id, :title, :content, :previous_module_id, :course_year_id, :version, :term], [
  ["ac3dc47f-e7fd-41b5-8c37-f096e4be451e", "Behaviour", "In this module you'll cover:\n\n* how to establish an effective learning environment\n* how to effectively manage behaviour\n* the importance of holding and promoting high expectations for all pupils", nil, "a4dc302c-ab71-4d7b-a10a-3116a778e8d5", 4, "spring"],
  ["e559d137-950b-4f5d-9878-8e14f0ea40db", "Instruction", "In this module you'll cover: \n\n* the link between effective instruction and pupil learning\n* the elements of explicit instruction and the ‘I-we-you’ model as a useful way of approaching this\n* how instruction can support more effective pupil thinking", "ac3dc47f-e7fd-41b5-8c37-f096e4be451e", "a4dc302c-ab71-4d7b-a10a-3116a778e8d5", 4, "spring"],
  ["6d8228f3-3fd8-4ac9-99d5-78c932af682d", "Subject", "In this module you'll cover:\n\n* the curriculum\n* your mental model of the subject or phase you teach and its implications for your planning\n* how to know what pupils have understood, the barriers you face in doing so and how to respond to their needs", "e559d137-950b-4f5d-9878-8e14f0ea40db", "a4dc302c-ab71-4d7b-a10a-3116a778e8d5", 4, "spring"],
  ["73ffd842-32ea-4019-97e3-08c7d392f4d0", "1: Establishing a positive climate for learning", "In this module you'll learn about teaching your pupils how to behave in your classroom, setting clear expectations and reinforcing these with consistent routines.\n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/i1ESaVcFPoA)\n", nil, "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["48c66862-8a65-4908-8fdc-eff63d632940", "2: How pupils learn ‒ memory and cognition", "In this module you'll gain an understanding of how the brain works, and how you can then design more effective learning for your pupils.  \n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/4FsOuLuiSls)\n", "73ffd842-32ea-4019-97e3-08c7d392f4d0", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["4fbb41be-5d5d-410a-a550-5d6e42cebdb8", "3: Developing effective classroom practice ‒ teaching and adapting", "In this module you'll focus on the fundamental techniques you can use to become a more effective teacher. \n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/s9FejY2jn68)", "48c66862-8a65-4908-8fdc-eff63d632940", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["1ee5b6c7-5dfd-4921-a8ab-091f4fda2659", "4: The importance of subject and curriculum knowledge", "In this module you'll learn practical ways to develop your subject and curriculum knowledge. \n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/NvHdUC04itc)", "4fbb41be-5d5d-410a-a550-5d6e42cebdb8", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["914e6384-016e-47b8-a2a9-ecd6914471c9", "5: Assessment, feedback and questioning", "In this module you'll work on developing effective assessment and feedback practices.\n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/lNs21BhfgkE)\n", "1ee5b6c7-5dfd-4921-a8ab-091f4fda2659", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["512255de-f403-462b-89b1-e4d7d98e7969", "6: A people profession", "In this module you'll focus on developing strong professional relationships to build the best outcomes for your pupils. \n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/sN2k_-jnqiM)", "914e6384-016e-47b8-a2a9-ecd6914471c9", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["357d7970-e1ca-42ec-a716-6fe4c4d5db5b", "7: Embedding a positive climate for learning", "In this module you'll look at what motivates pupils so you can develop a really purposeful learning environment. \n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/SjhGsyrewv8)", "512255de-f403-462b-89b1-e4d7d98e7969", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["7ead94a2-04f5-473b-869b-472bdfce3692", "8: How pupils learn – making it stick", "In this module you'll consider how you can make new learning stick over time so that pupils remember what they've been taught. \n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/14VyqJ4vAsk)", "357d7970-e1ca-42ec-a716-6fe4c4d5db5b", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["85ee0d84-beb4-4f33-aeb9-0ed4f43a96b8", "9: Enhancing classroom practice ‒ grouping and tailoring", "In this module you'll enhance your teaching effectiveness by learning advanced group and pair working skills. \n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/RSQBAZygnR4)", "7ead94a2-04f5-473b-869b-472bdfce3692", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["15eb3adb-e0b0-4578-8ca4-56864b25855d", "10: Revisiting the importance of subject and curriculum knowledge", "In this module you'll focus in how you can use your in-depth understanding of the subjects you teach to strengthen your pupils' knowledge. \n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/LShS6igaF1o)", "85ee0d84-beb4-4f33-aeb9-0ed4f43a96b8", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["83af890c-6092-40a4-87d1-b9f9575f3a95", "11: Deepening assessment, feedback and questioning", "In this module you'll build on your existing knowledge to develop further practical ways to hone your assessment, feedback and questioning techniques.\n\n[What you will learn video introduction](https://youtu.be/0D1-qOpgA9M)", "15eb3adb-e0b0-4578-8ca4-56864b25855d", "d7ac2099-81cb-4f95-9c32-ca68775c61d0", 4, "spring"],
  ["9d62c188-7269-429c-b1f6-e92102c57370", "1: How can you create an effective learning environment?", "In this module you'll explore what effective learning environments look like and strategies you can use to achieve them.\n", nil, "441979d3-787c-42bd-9072-2309125ef709", 4, "spring"],
  ["9e1b8b84-0fe6-4c6b-9103-f5f5cdef6aff", "2: How do pupils learn?", "In this module you'll explore the findings and evidence gathered during studies of how pupils learn, and the related implications for teaching.", "9d62c188-7269-429c-b1f6-e92102c57370", "441979d3-787c-42bd-9072-2309125ef709", 4, "spring"],
  ["55f7034a-3b4d-45e0-ae1a-ceda1c8a2fa9", "3: What makes classroom practice effective?", "In this module you'll hear an education expert talking about the features of effective classroom practice and why they are so important. You'll then explore the features in detail and have time to plan them into your sequences of lessons.", "9e1b8b84-0fe6-4c6b-9103-f5f5cdef6aff", "441979d3-787c-42bd-9072-2309125ef709", 4, "spring"],
  ["1bcccf21-4486-4167-b22d-f5901979119c", "4: How can you use assessment and feedback to greatest effect?", "In this module you'll hear from education experts about why assessment should be at the heart of your teaching. You'll also explore ways to give purposeful feedback to your pupils and what you can learn from summative data sets. ", "55f7034a-3b4d-45e0-ae1a-ceda1c8a2fa9", "441979d3-787c-42bd-9072-2309125ef709", 4, "spring"],
  ["f53a739d-7133-472a-90cb-5f31fa06c005", "5: How can you support all pupils to succeed?", "In this module you'll hear a variety of educational specialists talk about ways to support all pupils to succeed across the curriculum, and why this is so important.", "1bcccf21-4486-4167-b22d-f5901979119c", "441979d3-787c-42bd-9072-2309125ef709", 4, "spring"],
  ["d922d295-30b6-4bf4-ad74-134dbd925cae", "6: How to design a coherent curriculum", "In this module you'll learn how to design a carefully sequenced and coherent scheme of work and how this will improve learning for your pupils.\n", "f53a739d-7133-472a-90cb-5f31fa06c005", "441979d3-787c-42bd-9072-2309125ef709", 4, "spring"],
  ["6645d94d-05c5-4d36-82b4-b7a9ebe79c98", "1: Enabling pupil learning", "In this module you'll focus on how you set up your classroom as a learning environment. You'll be able to reflect on the different ways you can influence your environment, and learn practical strategies that keep pupils safe, motivated and focused on learning.", nil, "b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", 4, "spring"],
  ["88413299-e515-4fa5-b682-bf8986f902ca", "2: Engaging pupils in learning", "In this module you'll look at the impact of pupils’ prior knowledge on their learning and how knowledge changes through the cooperation of working and long-term memory. ", "6645d94d-05c5-4d36-82b4-b7a9ebe79c98", "b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", 4, "spring"],
  ["36cfa198-0983-418c-b279-7a085fef9f5c", "3: Developing quality pedagogy", "In this module you'll extend your knowledge of effective modelling that enables pupils to tackle difficult concepts. ", "88413299-e515-4fa5-b682-bf8986f902ca", "b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", 4, "spring"],
  ["f44425b3-191d-4dee-81de-8633be67582c", "4: Making productive use of assessment", "In this module you'll build on your existing knowledge of assessment principles.", "36cfa198-0983-418c-b279-7a085fef9f5c", "b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", 4, "spring"],
  ["b8731c76-6b20-42c6-9dfe-82b36fe469b1", "5: Fulfilling professional responsibilities", "In this module you'll consider what it means to be professional, and approaches to managing your professional development. ", "f44425b3-191d-4dee-81de-8633be67582c", "b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", 4, "spring"],
  ["e8bd30a9-e5be-4312-92ec-4cd9b52fab97", "6: Enabling pupil learning", "In this module you'll focus on one particular part of your teaching to evaluate the impact your practices have on your pupils. ", "b8731c76-6b20-42c6-9dfe-82b36fe469b1", "b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", 4, "spring"],
  ["4b79c261-b40d-44c4-8ec6-fa8dfdce89ca", "7: Engaging pupils in learning", "In this module you'll focus on how to improve your teaching without adding your workload. ", "e8bd30a9-e5be-4312-92ec-4cd9b52fab97", "b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", 4, "spring"],
  ["f89b9302-bb6b-4512-a3db-bf87565a561a", "8: Developing quality pedagogy and making productive use of assessment", "In this module you'll look at how to gather evidence about the impact your teaching is having, followed by practical tips on altering your practices to get better results. ", "4b79c261-b40d-44c4-8ec6-fa8dfdce89ca", "b61a7399-c503-4e37-81af-e45bdaddd93c", 4, "spring"]
])
